      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      48.2,
      138.74,
      290.72,
      272.21
    ],
    "text": "BE it enacted by the Parliament of the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka as follows:- 1. This Act may be cited as the Strategic Development Projects (Amendment) Act, No. 26 of 2025. 2. Section 2 of the Strategic Development Projects Act, No. 14 of 2008 (hereinafter referred to as the \u201cprincipal enactment\u201d), as last amended by Act, No. 12 of 2011, is hereby further amended in proviso thereof, by the substitution for the words \u201ctwenty-five years.\u201d, of the words \u201cten years.\u201d.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      48.2,
      282.58,
      290.71,
      308.21
    ],
    "text": "3. Section 3 of the principal enactment is hereby repealed and the following section is substituted therefor: -",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      102.2,
      318.58,
      290.71,
      368.21
    ],
    "text": "3. (1) The Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall, subject to the criteria as may be prescribed, identify any proposed project as a Strategic Development Project.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-BoldMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      102.2,
      378.74,
      290.71,
      440.21
    ],
    "text": "(2) Upon being identified the proposed project as a Strategic Development Project, the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka shall refer such project proposal to the Ministry of Finance for ex-ante cost-benefit analysis.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      102.2,
      450.74,
      290.71,
      536.21
    ],
    "text": "(3) The Ministry of Finance shall, with the technical input from the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka, carry out such ex-ante cost-benefit analysis of the project and submit a recommendation to the Board of Investment of Sri Lanka within one month from the date of such reference under subsection (2).",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      10.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      300.0,
      176.88,
      331.78,
      187.66
    ],
